{{!
    @template mod_fastpix/processing

    Asset is uploading or transcoding. The poller AMD module polls
    mod_fastpix_get_player_state and, when the asset goes ready, swaps the
    CONTENTS of [data-region="fastpix-processing"] in place (node.replaceChildren)
    with the rendered mod_fastpix/player_wrapper. A meta-refresh in <head>
    (set in view.php) is the JS-free fallback.

    SWAP CONTRACT (critical):
      The root [data-region="fastpix-processing"] is a PLAIN container with NO
      framing of its own. The dark 16:9 loader frame is a CHILD inside it, so
      replaceChildren() cleanly drops the frame and drops in the player wrapper.
      Do NOT move framing onto the root, or the swap inherits stale chrome.

    Hard contract:
      [data-region="fastpix-processing"] with data-cm-id, data-activity-id,
      and data-upload-session-id (when set).
      [data-region="fastpix-processing-fallback"] hidden by default.
      The inline-JS block inits mod_fastpix/processing_state_poller via
      init(cm_id, upload_session_id).
      String helpers: processing_title / processing_message /
      processing_progress_aria / processing_max_polls.

    Context variables:
      * activity_id        int
      * cm_id              int
      * upload_session_id  int|null
      * activity_name      string

    Design: a DARK charcoal 16:9 frame matching the player canvas, with the same
    border-radius (14px) + elevation as .mod_fastpix-player-wrapper, plus a faint
    brand-pink glow so the processing screen reads as premium and the
    processing -> player swap feels seamless. Self-contained dark, so it reads
    correctly on both light and dark page themes. Brand colour: #ec1e5b.

    NOTE: never write a curly-brace pair inside this comment block. Mustache
    treats the first closing pair it sees as the comment terminator and leaks the
    remainder as literal text, which breaks the client-side swap (a stray leading
    text node is parsed by jQuery as a CSS selector and throws).

    Example context (json):
    {
        "activity_id": 1,
        "cm_id": 2,
        "upload_session_id": 3,
        "activity_name": "Welcome video"
    }
}}
<div class="mod_fastpix-processing"
     data-region="fastpix-processing"
     data-cm-id="{{cm_id}}"
     data-activity-id="{{activity_id}}"
     {{#upload_session_id}}data-upload-session-id="{{upload_session_id}}"{{/upload_session_id}}>


    <div class="fastpix-prep-frame">
        <div class="fastpix-prep-spinner"
             role="progressbar"
             aria-label="{{#str}}processing_progress_aria, mod_fastpix{{/str}}"
             aria-busy="true"></div>

        <h1 class="fastpix-prep-title">
            {{#str}}processing_title, mod_fastpix{{/str}}
        </h1>
        <p class="fastpix-prep-lede">
            {{#str}}processing_message, mod_fastpix{{/str}}
        </p>

        <p data-region="fastpix-processing-fallback"
           class="fastpix-prep-fallback"
           hidden>
            {{#str}}processing_max_polls, mod_fastpix{{/str}}
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

{{#js}}
require(['mod_fastpix/processing_state_poller'], function(Poller) {
    if (Poller && typeof Poller.init === 'function') {
        Poller.init({{cm_id}}, {{#upload_session_id}}{{upload_session_id}}{{/upload_session_id}}{{^upload_session_id}}null{{/upload_session_id}});
    }
});
{{/js}}
